[{"type":"{{","value":[["pagebanner"],["Orkney Islands banner.JPG"],["unesco=yes"]]},"\nThe ",{"type":"'''","value":[{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.visitorkney.com Orkney Islands"]}]}," are an archipelago of approximately 70 islands some 10 miles (16 km) off the northern coast of ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Scotland"]]},".\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Understand"]},"\nThe Orkney Islands have been settled since the Neolithic Period. There is plenty to do on the islands. They are easy to navigate. The islands are great for culture holidays and sight-seeing\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Islands"]},"\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["Image:Orkney map.png"],["thumb"],["Map of the Orkney Islands"]]},"\n\n",{"type":"*","value":[{"type":"[[","value":[["Eday"]]},", the Isthmus Island with excellent walks. "]},{"type":"*","value":[{"type":"[[","value":[["Egilsay"]]},", where Earl Magnus was martyred. "]},{"type":"*","value":[{"type":"[[","value":[["Flotta"]]},", location of oil terminal"]},{"type":"*","value":[{"type":"[[","value":[["Hoy"]]},", the High Island.  Hike through R.S.P.B. Nature Reserve to cliffs overlooking the Old Man of Hoy sea stack.  "]},{"type":"*","value":[{"type":"[[","value":[["Mainland (Orkney)"],["Mainland"]]},", Orkney's largest island where 2\/3 of the Isles' population resides."]},{"type":"*","value":[{"type":"[[","value":[["North Ronaldsay"]]},", well-worth the trip if only to climb to the top of the new lighthouse for fantastic views, and to see Old Beacon, the third oldest lighthouse in Scotland."]},{"type":"*","value":[{"type":"[[","value":[["Papa Westray"]]},", referred to locally as \"Papay\", the island is home to the oldest site in Orkney, Knap of Howar. "]},{"type":"*","value":[{"type":"[[","value":[["Rousay"]]},", the Egypt of the North with a large concentration of spectacular archaeological sites. "]},{"type":"*","value":[{"type":"[[","value":[["Sanday"]]},", aptly named the Sand Island for its beautiful beaches."]},{"type":"*","value":[{"type":"[[","value":[["Shapinsay"]]},", a short ferry sailing from Kirkwall and home to Balfour Castle."]},{"type":"*","value":[{"type":"[[","value":[["Stronsay"]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[{"type":"[[","value":[["Westray"]]},", Queen o' the Orkney Islands.  Excellent place to spot puffins in late spring to find the best fish & chips in Orkney at the Pierowall Hotel."]},{"type":"*","value":[{"type":"[[","value":[["Wyre"]]}]},"\nSouth Isles connected by the Churchill Barriers:\n",{"type":"*","value":["Burray"]},{"type":"*","value":["Glimsholm"]},{"type":"*","value":["Lambholm, home of the stunning Italian Chapel."]},{"type":"*","value":["South Ronaldsay"]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Towns and Villages"]},"\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["Towns"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[{"type":"[[","value":[["Kirkwall"]]}," - the administrative capital of the Orkney Islands"]},{"type":"*","value":[{"type":"[[","value":[["Stromness"]]}," - attractive port and the Orkney's second town"]},"\n",{"type":"===","value":["Villages"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[{"type":"[[","value":[["Birsay"]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[{"type":"[[","value":[["Lyness"]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[{"type":"[[","value":[["St Margaret's Hope"]]}]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Get in"]},"\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["By plane"]},"\n",{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.flybe.com\/ Flybe"]}," offers flights to Kirkwall, Orkney from Edinburgh, Glasgow, Inverness, Aberdeen and Sumburgh. Aircraft are operated by Loganair.\n\nOrkney also has the shortest commercial flight in the world, at just under 2 minutes!\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["By boat"]},"\nRo\/Ro Ferries:\n \n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"'''","value":["Scrabster to Stromness, Orkney Mainland"]},":  90-minute sailings offered 3 times a day, 7 days a week.  Service provided by Northlink Ferries ",{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.northlinkferries.co.uk\/"]},".  Approx. 30 minute drive to Kirkwall from Stromness."]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"'''","value"